cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CC 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language semantics and the representation of meaning in computational linguistics. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as these fields often use vector representations for natural language processing tasks. Additionally, it could be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it proposes a framework for representing meaning in terms of vectors, which involves mathematical abstractions and algebraic structures. Finally, it could be classified under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as it discusses the complexity of computing the context-theoretic probability of a string.
